<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She found fame as Kelly on Beverly Hills, 90210.</p>

<p>And on Tuesday, Jennie Garth was spotted out and about in Los Angeles,  barely recognizable thanks to a wide-brimmed hat and face mask. </p>

<p>The actress, 48, wore a coordinated blue ensemble on the sunny fall day.</p>

<p>Covered up: Former Beverly Hills, 90210 star Jennie Garth wore a coordinated blue ensemble as she headed to a golf course in LA on Tuesday wearing a sunhat and face mask</p>

<p>Garth paired a sleeveless collared shirt with a sports skirt and designer trainers as she arrived at a golf course.</p>

<p>Her hat was pulled down over her blonde hair that was tied back from her face and she sported black-framed spectacles and a disposable mask.</p>

<p>She was accompanied by her actor husband Dave Abrams, 39.  </p>

<p>Recreation: The actress, 48, paired a sleeveless collared shirt with a sports skirt and designer trainers and sported a pair of black-framed sunglasses</p>

<p>Garth and Abrams began dating in fall 2014  following the actress' divorce from second husband Peter Facinelli the previous year. </p>

<p>They became engaged in April 2015 and exchanged vows in July that year.  </p>

<p>However, they separated in 2017 and in April 2018 they filed for divorce. But then in February 2019, they got back together and had the divorce proceedings dismissed.</p>

<p>In an interview with People, Gary had explained: 'Dave and I fell in love really fast and got married within six months,' Garth said. 'We rushed it too much, and that hurt us.'</p>

<p>Rocky road: Garth and actor Dave Abrams, pictured in November 2019, married in 2015 after a few months of dating. They split in 2017 and planned to divorce but then reconciled last year</p>

<p>Garth, who was married to first husband, musician Daniel B. Clark from 1994 to 1996, told the publication that the thought of going through a third divorce 'really devastated me.' </p>

<p>She told People: 'We definitely had to just part ways completely. And just when I felt whole again, we started hanging out. He needed to go away and figure everything out.' </p>

<p>She added: 'Marriage is not like a fairy tale. It's a process, and it's about continuously wanting to make it better.'</p>

<p>90s star: Garth found fame as Kelly on Beverly Hills, 90210. She was previously married to musician  Daniel B. Clark from 1994 to 1996 and Peter Facinelli from 2001 to 2013 </p>
